00:40:26,640 --> 00:40:29,030
She might even get an inheritance from an elderly living alone.

477
00:40:29,030 --> 00:40:32,400
That's a bit too far-reaching.

478
00:40:32,400 --> 00:40:35,800
They say if coincidences keep repeating, it's a scam.

479
00:40:38,980 --> 00:40:43,360
What are you doing? You receive gifts instead of giving them away.

480
00:40:49,350 --> 00:40:52,090
I thought it was Korean beef ribs.

481
00:40:52,830 --> 00:40:55,110
They're VIPs for a reason.

482
00:40:55,110 --> 00:40:58,170
They want you to exchange it if you don't like it.

483
00:40:58,880 --> 00:41:01,020
How much does it cost?

484
00:41:04,090 --> 00:41:06,940
 Total: 1,100,000 won

485
00:41:15,970 --> 00:41:18,080
Welcome.

486
00:41:19,250 --> 00:41:23,140
 Customer No. 8, come to the desk No. 3.

487
00:41:26,480 --> 00:41:29,360
Should I make you something with the groceries I got this morning?

488
00:41:29,360 --> 00:41:31,000
You'd create trash.

489
00:41:31,000 --> 00:41:32,820
I just eat like this and throw away the containers.

490
00:41:32,820 --> 00:41:35,160
I don't even do the dishes.

491
00:41:36,520 --> 00:41:38,570
It's all right.

492
00:41:39,270 --> 00:41:41,750
Just wait a moment.

493
00:41:42,760 --> 00:41:44,800
It's the amount I told you this morning, right?

494
00:41:44,800 --> 00:41:46,610
Yes.

495
00:41:49,540 --> 00:41:52,580
It's 30 million won in 50,000 won bills.

496
00:41:58,390 --> 00:42:01,650
You never get it wrong. It's exactly that.

497
00:42:05,260 --> 00:42:07,310
It's a myeongran* stew. 
