520
00:45:16,940 --> 00:45:19,710
Ms. Yu, I heard you got into a car accident.

521
00:45:21,010 --> 00:45:22,740
I...

522
00:45:23,980 --> 00:45:26,070
actually...

523
00:45:26,760 --> 00:45:29,080
What happened?

524
00:45:33,380 --> 00:45:35,790
Did you get hurt?

525
00:45:46,610 --> 00:45:48,710
It's all right.

526
00:45:48,710 --> 00:45:50,970
It's all right, I said.

527
00:45:55,200 --> 00:45:58,700
 SD Savings Bank

528
00:45:58,700 --> 00:46:01,790
Claim the repair bill when you get it. The bank will pay for it.

529
00:46:01,790 --> 00:46:04,190
Eonni, do you have 5,000 won?

530
00:46:04,190 --> 00:46:05,740
- Is it not balancing out?
- How nice.

531
00:46:05,740 --> 00:46:08,760
- I don't have cash.
- You get a vacation reward.

532
00:46:09,860 --> 00:46:12,420
I checked three times.

533
00:46:24,540 --> 00:46:27,960
You don't have any review requests, right? Right?

534
00:46:27,960 --> 00:46:30,260
Enjoy the long holiday, then.

535
00:46:30,260 --> 00:46:32,440
Yes sir! Have a nice weekend!

536
00:46:32,440 --> 00:46:34,300
Bye.

537
00:47:52,520 --> 00:47:54,580
 No.

538
00:48:17,550 --> 00:48:21,080
 Oh Suk Ja

539
00:48:35,860 --> 00:48:38,200
I scared you, didn't I?

540
00:48:38,200 --> 00:48:43,600
Where have you been rolling around that your shirt is all wrinkled?

541
00:48:44,250 --> 00:48:48,480
Your branch must've started working overtime.

542
00:48:48,480 --> 00:48:50,040
Come on in.

543
00:48:50,040 --> 00:48:52,570
Please call the branch.

544
00:48:53,220 --> 00:48:57,130
You met him again, didn't you? That son of a bitch.

545
00:49:01,690 --> 00:49:04,980
- What do you mean—
- You said you know how to contact him.

546
00:49:04,980 --> 00:49:06,470
Go tell him.

547
00:49:06,470 --> 00:49:11,500
The interest will go up to 40% starting next month.

548
00:49:12,160 --> 00:49:14,660
You gave your grandson a private loan?

549
00:49:15,370 --> 00:49:17,790
He's still a student.

550
00:49:22,750 --> 00:49:28,690
It seems like he borrowed money from the man who used to work for me.

551
00:49:28,690 --> 00:49:33,530
He got the loan without collateral, just because he's my grandson.

552
00:49:33,530 --> 00:49:36,760
He's now asking me to pay off his debt.

553
00:49:36,760 --> 00:49:42,300
Since I've been making payments, I can raise the interest rate all I want.

554
00:49:42,300 --> 00:49:44,010
Go and tell him.

555
00:49:44,010 --> 00:49:48,020
The interest rate is 40%.

556
00:49:49,710 --> 00:49:55,130
If he doesn't send the interest money, I'll send a collection agent to his place.

557
00:49:56,520 --> 00:49:59,230
Your grandson has a father who's in a nursing home—

558
00:49:59,230 --> 00:50:01,100
Look at this!

559
00:50:01,100 --> 00:50:03,620
You're close enough to know that?

560
00:50:03,620 --> 00:50:08,820
Your grandson... is struggling a lot.

561
00:50:08,820 --> 00:50:10,760
So?

562
00:50:10,760 --> 00:50:15,620
You think I won't get my money back?

563
00:50:15,620 --> 00:50:19,520
I don't give out loans based on the collateral.

564
00:50:19,520 --> 00:50:23,030
I do it because I know I will be repaid.

565
00:50:23,830 --> 00:50:26,750
All of his four limbs are intact.

566
00:50:26,750 --> 00:50:30,700
His eyes are healthy, too.

567
00:50:32,090 --> 00:50:36,410
Tons of people would pay money for them.

568
00:50:52,870 --> 00:50:56,100
I didn't realize it got so late.

569
00:50:57,530 --> 00:51:00,140
You're eating a burger. Should I make you dinner?

570
00:51:00,140 --> 00:51:02,330
It's all right.

571
00:51:02,330 --> 00:51:05,210
The vice president was right. It's not too bad.

572
00:51:05,970 --> 00:51:08,670
He apparently likes artisan burgers.

573
00:51:11,940 --> 00:51:13,820
Honey.

574
00:51:14,850 --> 00:51:16,960
Where's your wedding ring?

575
00:51:19,630 --> 00:51:23,100
I took it off because my fingers got puffy.

576
00:51:25,840 --> 00:51:29,910
Did you put our mobile somewhere?

577
00:51:32,620 --> 00:51:35,840
You haven't said anything all this time.

578
00:51:36,590 --> 00:51:39,140
I heard from the vice president's wife.

579
00:51:39,140 --> 00:51:42,600
It's not good to keep objects that sway in the house.

580
00:51:43,820 --> 00:51:47,280
I guess you talk to her sometimes.

581
00:51:47,280 --> 00:51:49,440
Good work.

582
00:51:50,260 --> 00:51:52,090
You're doing a great job.

583
00:51:52,090 --> 00:51:55,100
-Would you like some juice?
- No, no, it's all right.

584
00:51:55,100 --> 00:51:58,820
You must be tired from working your job.

585
00:52:08,830 --> 00:52:10,820
Honey.

586
00:52:13,200 --> 00:52:16,000
The zipper looked too stiff.

587
00:52:17,540 --> 00:52:22,450
I noticed at the airport that a lot of people carry purses without zippers.

588
00:52:22,450 --> 00:52:25,500
I'll get you one from my next business trip.

589
00:52:25,500 --> 00:52:28,070
You should start replacing things here and there.

590
00:52:28,070 --> 00:52:33,150
You'll be hanging out with different kinds of people now.

591
00:52:36,680 --> 00:52:38,360
Give me the juice.

592
00:53:00,270 --> 00:53:04,370
 I don't give loans based on the collateral.

593
00:53:04,370 --> 00:53:08,210
 I do it because I know I will be repaid.

594
00:53:08,210 --> 00:53:11,300
 All of his four limbs are intact.

595
00:53:11,300 --> 00:53:15,340
 His eyes are healthy, too.

596
00:53:16,610 --> 00:53:20,820
 Tons of people would pay money for them.

597
00:53:43,810 --> 00:53:49,390
 Oh Suk Ja - 30 million

598
00:54:14,320 --> 00:54:17,370
Ma'am, would you like to try them out?

599
00:54:20,300 --> 00:54:23,610
I'll have everything from here to here.

600
00:54:23,610 --> 00:54:25,360
I'll pay in a lump sum.

601
00:54:25,360 --> 00:54:27,820
All of these?

602
00:54:27,820 --> 00:54:29,450
Yes.

603
00:54:36,320 --> 00:54:39,590
You have to wait two years if you don't get it this week.

604
00:54:39,590 --> 00:54:42,170
Would you like to be on the waiting list?

605
00:54:45,090 --> 00:54:47,830
I'll just get the wallet today. How much is it?

606
00:54:47,830 --> 00:54:49,760
It will be 1 million and 571,000 won.

607
00:54:49,760 --> 00:54:53,110
- I'll pay in a lump sum.
- Yes, madam.

608
00:55:08,600 --> 00:55:13,900
Do you need more than this to pay off your private loan?

609
00:55:19,480 --> 00:55:22,620
I didn't tell you about my situation to borrow money.

610
00:55:25,100 --> 00:55:28,220
I'll just take 3%.

611
00:55:28,220 --> 00:55:31,570
I was going to use this on that purse earlier.

612
00:55:31,570 --> 00:55:35,480
I get a discount if I pay in cash.

613
00:55:41,340 --> 00:55:45,220
I was just thinking of shopping, but I think it'd be

614
00:55:47,320 --> 00:55:50,440
better to spend the money this way.

615
00:56:04,670 --> 00:56:07,530
- To a foreign country? 
 - Yes.

616
00:56:07,530 --> 00:56:10,610
They'll announce the expatriate employee after this business trip.

617
00:56:10,610 --> 00:56:14,840
If I work overseas for two years, I'd be guaranteed an executive promotion.

618
00:56:15,800 --> 00:56:18,850
Just as I thought, it was high-risk, high-return.

619
00:56:18,850 --> 00:56:24,490
The executive director said the vice president recommended me strongly.

620
00:56:24,490 --> 00:56:26,800
You should prepare for it, too.

621
00:56:31,660 --> 00:56:35,170
That's just your plan.

622
00:56:35,990 --> 00:56:39,220
Even if you get promoted, I want to keep working.

623
00:56:39,220 --> 00:56:43,580
I'm getting good results, too.

624
00:56:43,580 --> 00:56:46,950
If you're selected as an expatriate employee officially,

625
00:56:47,700 --> 00:56:50,080
let's discuss it then.

626
00:56:58,740 --> 00:57:03,040
Gosh, what are you doing? Why are you doing this at my shop?

627
00:57:06,310 --> 00:57:09,140
Min Jae! Min Jae! Min Jae!

628
00:57:18,580 --> 00:57:21,020
They really are healthy.

629
00:57:21,020 --> 00:57:23,400
Those are pretty corneas.

630
00:57:23,400 --> 00:57:26,480
- It'd cost quite a bit.
- I'll pay him. I'll pay him, I said!

631
00:57:26,480 --> 00:57:28,280
I know. I know.

632
00:57:28,280 --> 00:57:30,810
You wouldn't be human if you didn't pay after all this.

633
00:57:30,810 --> 00:57:35,250
Anyway, do you want to borrow the money to compensate for this bar?

634
00:57:35,250 --> 00:57:37,560
Their business got ruined because of you.

635
00:57:37,560 --> 00:57:40,910
The interest rate went up because your payments were late a lot.

636
00:57:40,910 --> 00:57:44,650
The monthly rate will go up to 40% starting today.

637
00:58:07,900 --> 00:58:10,180
 Closed temporarily due to personal reasons

638
00:58:42,960 --> 00:58:45,740
 Did you feel offended?

639
00:58:45,740 --> 00:58:48,940
I don't need that money.

640
00:58:53,010 --> 00:58:55,320
You did that on purpose, right?

641
00:58:56,180 --> 00:58:58,770
I appreciate the suggestion.

642
00:58:58,770 --> 00:59:04,050
I really appreciate it, but could you ask me some kind of favor?

643
00:59:05,290 --> 00:59:08,660
If there's anything I can do for borrowing that money,

644
00:59:09,530 --> 00:59:11,950
feel free to ask me.

645
00:59:21,920 --> 00:59:25,650
I need to ask you a favor. Can we meet?

646
00:59:27,880 --> 00:59:30,460
 There's something I want you to do for me.

647
00:59:30,460 --> 00:59:33,790
 I'll wait in front of the department store.

648
00:59:33,790 --> 00:59:36,270
 You can find me, right?

649
00:59:40,000 --> 00:59:45,800
♫  I entered the darkness  ♫

650
00:59:51,150 --> 00:59:56,660
♫  And walked endlessly  ♫

651
01:00:02,360 --> 01:00:07,810
♫  I entered the rain  ♫

652
01:00:13,400 --> 01:00:19,220
♫  and kept walking  ♫

653
01:00:24,660 --> 01:00:30,260
♫  Only on Sunday afternoon  ♫

654
01:00:35,870 --> 01:00:41,270
♫  it rained beautifully  ♫

655
01:00:46,990 --> 01:00:53,040
♫  Only on Sunday afternoon  ♫

656
01:00:58,000 --> 01:01:04,040
♫  A gentile night fell  ♫

657
01:01:12,950 --> 01:01:14,790
It's dripping.

658
01:01:26,200 --> 01:01:28,210
It's all right.

659
01:01:28,210 --> 01:01:31,780
I'm doing my favorite thing in the world right now.

660
01:01:44,170 --> 01:01:47,380
What favor did you want to ask me?

661
01:01:50,560 --> 01:01:55,540
Please finish a script in a week.

662
01:01:57,480 --> 01:01:59,690
I'll invest in it.

663
01:02:15,220 --> 01:02:17,430
Is it for two people?

664
01:02:20,580 --> 01:02:22,750
Just one person.

665
01:02:26,810 --> 01:02:29,630
Is staying long-term possible?

666
01:03:01,610 --> 01:03:03,460
Yes, Ms. Na.

667
01:03:03,460 --> 01:03:05,280
 Where are you right now?

668
01:03:05,280 --> 01:03:07,760
 Come to the bank immediately!

669
01:03:36,700 --> 01:03:38,820
 I got caught.

670
01:03:40,400 --> 01:03:42,990
What's all this?

671
01:03:45,220 --> 01:03:47,420
Hey, you came.

672
01:04:07,990 --> 01:04:14,990

673
01:04:21,300 --> 01:04:26,570
 Pale Moon 
 Preview

674
01:04:26,570 --> 01:04:28,600
 Whenever one's sales go up suddenly,

675
01:04:28,600 --> 01:04:31,100
 or they suddenly start spending money, something always goes wrong.

676
01:04:31,100 --> 01:04:33,590
 Not just 10 or 20 million, but 100 million?

677
01:04:33,590 --> 01:04:35,300
 Several 100 million?

678
01:04:35,300 --> 01:04:36,910
 How about you, Yi Hwa?

679
01:04:36,910 --> 01:04:39,240
 Was it like his teenage first love or something?

680
01:04:39,240 --> 01:04:42,530
 I wanted to see you from the start.

681
01:04:42,530 --> 01:04:44,780
 It's best to stay where you are, Yi Hwa.

682
01:04:44,780 --> 01:04:46,420
 How much will it be?

683
01:04:46,420 --> 01:04:48,520
 How much do you want?

684
01:04:49,330 --> 01:04:52,240
 This money is for protecting you.
